TRANSMISSION SYSTEM DESIGN

3.1 Antenna System

```
PARABOLIC REFLECTOR:
  Diameter: 100 m (optimal: 305 m equivalent to Arecibo)
  Focal length: 30 m (f/D = 0.3)
  Surface material: Aluminum panels with active adjustment
  Surface accuracy: 1.05 cm RMS (λ/20 at 21 cm)
  Pointing accuracy: 0.0001° (0.36 arcseconds)
  Slew rate: 0.1°/second maximum

FEED SYSTEM:
  Type: Cassegrain dual-reflector with Gregory optics
  Feed horn: Corrugated for circular polarization
  Low-noise amplifier: Cryogenic HEMT, 20 K noise temperature
  Bandwidth: 1 MHz tunable, 10 Hz operational
  Phase stability: 0.1° over 1 hour

SITE REQUIREMENTS:
  Radio quiet zone: Natural RFI < -200 dBW/Hz
  Atmospheric conditions: Precipitable water vapor < 1 mm
  Altitude: > 3,000 m (reduced atmospheric absorption)
  Geological stability: Seismic activity < Richter 3.0
  Political stability: 100-year land lease guaranteed
```

3.2 Transmitter Chain

```
FREQUENCY GENERATION:
  Primary reference: Hydrogen maser atomic clock
  Stability: 10⁻¹⁵ over 24 hours (Allan deviation)
  Phase noise: -120 dBc/Hz at 1 kHz offset
  Digital synthesis: DDS with 48-bit frequency resolution

POWER AMPLIFICATION:
  Final stage: Multiple klystrons or solid-state amplifiers
  Output power: 1 MW continuous wave (2 MW pulsed)
  Efficiency: >60% overall
  Cooling: Liquid helium cryogenic system
  Protection: Arc detection, VSWR monitoring, thermal sensors

MODULATION & EXCITER:
  BPSK modulator: I/Q modulator with 180° phase switching
  Rise time: 10% of bit period (0.7 ns)
  Spurious emissions: -80 dBc minimum
  Filtering: Root-raised cosine, α = 0.35
```

3.3 Control & Monitoring

```
SOFTWARE SYSTEM:
  Tracking: Precise ephemeris calculation for targets
  Modulation: Real-time bitstream generation
  Monitoring: Power, phase, frequency, temperature sensors
  Logging: Complete transmission parameters archive
  Redundancy: Hot-standby for all critical components

CALIBRATION:
  Daily: Noise diode calibration for receiver
  Weekly: Pointing model verification using quasars
  Monthly: Full system gain calibration
  Annual: Surface adjustment using holography
```

