7.3 Planetary Protection Protocol

```
PRIME DIRECTIVE ADAPTATION:
  1. No transmission to stars with confirmed biosignatures
  2. No Earth location data (only galactic coordinates)
  3. No military or technological information
  4. No appeals for help or resources
  5. Focus on universal, non-threatening content

PRE-TRANSMISSION REVIEW:
  Committee: International panel of scientists, ethicists, theologians
  Process: Annual review of transmission content
  Veto power: 2/3 majority required to block transmission
  Appeal: Scientific consensus override available

POST-TRANSMISSION MONITORING:
  Continuous: Signal verification and logging
  Annual: Review of transmission ethics
  Decadal: Comprehensive impact assessment
  Century: Long-term effects evaluation
```

